The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 15000 expected for city marathon

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: The Airtel Calcutta Marathon the third year of the longest race in the city will be run on Sunday. 

This years marathon boasts a budget of Rs 60 lakh. The mens event, to be run over 42.195 kms, offers a prize money of Rs 2.5 lakh while the womens event, which will cover 10.5 kms, carries a prize of Rs 65,000. There will also be a 4 km Fun Run for All. 

Two thousand volunteers will be in service with booths situated every two and a half kms of the route. The organisers are expecting about 15,000 participants. 

The main marathon will be flagged off at 7.30 am from Red Road. 

Prasun Mukherjee, commissioner of police is the chairman of the organising committee, while chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee is the patron-in chief. 




